      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:29:1",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ قَالَ لِامْرَأَتِهِ يَا زَانِيَةُ أَنَا زَنَيْتُ بِكِ قَالَ عَلَيْهِ حَدٌّ وَاحِدٌ لِقَذْفِهِ إِيَّاهَا وَ أَمَّا قَوْلُهُ أَنَا زَنَيْتُ بِكِ فَلَا حَدَّ فِيهِ إِلَّا أَنْ يَشْهَدَ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ أَرْبَعَ شَهَادَاتٍ بِالزِّنَى عِنْدَ الْإِمَامِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ibn Mahboub, from Al A’ala Bin Razeyn and Abu Ayoub, form Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> regarding a man who said to his wife, ‘O adulteress, I have committed adultery with you’. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Upon him is one Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) due to slandering her, and as for his words, ‘I have commited adultery with you’, so there is no Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) with regards to it, except if he were to testify against her with four testimonies with the adultery in the presence of the Imam<sup>asws</sup>’."
        ]
      }
    },
